body:
i had the same problem with polish characters. i tested it on  5.x versions (win 7, apache2.4, php5.4.x) and my workaround is translating paths and filenames to/from utf8. i made some modifications to: lib/files/storage/mappedlocal.php (this is used for windows filesystem). 

method mappedlocal->opendir use php method readdir which not return utf-8 names. my changes:

    public function opendir($path) {
        $files = array('.', '..');
        $physicalpath = $this->buildpath($path, true, false);//modification
        $logicalpath = $this->mapper->physicaltologic($physicalpath);
        $dh = opendir(self::fromutf8($physicalpath));//modification
        if(is_resource($dh)) {
            while (($file = readdir($dh)) !== false) {
                if ($file === '.' or $file === '..') {
                    continue;
                }
                $file = self::toutf8($file);//modification
                $logicalfilepath = $this->mapper->physicaltologic($physicalpath.'/'.$file);

                $file= $this->mapper->striprootfolder($logicalfilepath, $logicalpath);
                $file = $this->stripleading($file);
                $files[]= $file;
            }
        }

        \oc\files\stream\dir::register('local-win32'.$path, $files);
        return opendir('fakedir://local-win32'.$path);
    }



next i added two private methods:

    private static function toutf8($value){
        return iconv('', 'utf-8', $value);
    }

    private static function fromutf8($value){
        return iconv('utf-8', '', $value);
    }


and last change relates to method buildpath:

    private function buildpath($path, $create=true, $convertencoding=true) {//modification
        $path = $this->stripleading($path);
        $fullpath = $this->datadir.$path;
        $path = $this->mapper->logictophysical($fullpath, $create);
        //modification
        if($convertencoding){
            $path = self::fromutf8($path);
        }
        return $path;
    }


now i can listing and open files with special characters (f.e. ä™ã³ä…å›å‚å¼åºä‡å„ä˜ã“ä„åšå?å»å¹ä†åƒ).unfortunately, i did not test how it works in other versions of windows  (not pl).
